item.title: Fundraising UK veteran tops music charts
item.description: A World War II veteran who raised millions for charity has become the oldest person to top Britain's main music chart.

item.title: Trump signs off on $US484 billion package
item.description: US President Donald Trump has signed into law the latest stimulus package, worth $US484b ($A760b), designed to help small businesses and hospitals while providing more funding for testing.

item.title: Victorians to honour Anzac Day at home
item.description: The Shrine of Remembrance is empty as Victorians stay home this Anzac Day.

item.title: NZ’s Ardern leads Anzac Day tributes
item.description: New Zealand's leaders have risen at dawn on Anzac Day, defying the national lockdown to recognise past sacrifices and understand the country's war-woven threads.

item.title: Meghan awaits ruling on newspaper case
item.description: Meghan, the Duchess of Sussex, is awaiting a ruling on the first stage of her privacy claim against a British newspaper that published part of a letter to her estranged father.

item.title: Stocks fall on worries over EU stimulus
item.description: Global have fallen on Friday, spurred by delays to an agreement on divisive details of the European Union's stimulus package and doubts about progress in the development of drugs to treat COVID-19.

item.title: Aussies gather on COVID-19-free Antarctica
item.description: While those in Australia have been forced to distance on Anzac Day, the nation's Antarctic expeditioners have come together to pay their respects.

item.title: Boy, 6, and woman stabbed in Sydney unit
item.description: A six-year-old boy and a woman have been stabbed in a domestic incident in western Sydney.

item.title: Aussie to ‘walk in faith’ in vaccine trial
item.description: An Australian man who is testing a potential coronavirus vaccine in the UK says he is taking a "walk in faith".

item.title: Almost 1m businesses want JobKeeper pay
item.description: Around 900,000 businesses have indicated they want a share of the federal government's historic $130 billion JobKeeper payment to cushion the impact of coronavirus.
